Generate a professional visual (diagram, infographic, illustration) from text using Napkin AI.

IMPORTANT - ASYNC WORKFLOW (you MUST follow these steps):
1. Call napkin_generate_visual -> returns a request_id immediately
2. Call napkin_check_status(request_id) repeatedly every 3-5 seconds
3. Continue polling until status is "completed" or "failed"
4. When completed, you get file URLs in generated_files array
5. Optionally call napkin_download_visual to save files to disk

VISUAL QUERY EXAMPLES (use visual_query to request specific diagram types):
- "mindmap", "timeline", "flowchart", "comparison", "hierarchy"
- "process", "cycle", "matrix", "funnel", "pyramid"
- Omit visual_query to let Napkin auto-select the best layout

STYLE IDS: Visit https://app.napkin.ai to find style IDs. Built-in styles include categories like colorful, casual, hand-drawn, formal, and monochrome. Copy the style ID from the app.

QUICK START EXAMPLES:
- Simple: { "content": "Three pillars of product development: research, build, iterate" }
- With style: { "content": "Our quarterly results...", "format": "png", "style_id": "YOUR_STYLE_ID" }
- Mindmap: { "content": "AI ecosystem overview...", "visual_query": "mindmap" }
- Multiple variations: { "content": "Project timeline...", "number_of_visuals": 3 }
- High-res PNG: { "content": "Architecture diagram...", "format": "png", "width": 2400 }
- Dark mode: { "content": "Data flow...", "color_mode": "dark", "transparent_background": true }

DO NOT assume the generation is complete immediately - you MUST poll napkin_check_status.

